  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "The parameters of the choice model are mostly assumed to be unknown and thus need to be estimated from data, such that statistical errors in the parameters are unavoidable (Désir et al. 2023).",
    "The optimal assortment decision is then made based on the estimated parameter values while ignoring any uncertainty associated with these estimates (Rusmevichientong and Topaloglu 2012).",
    "To overcome this issue, an uncertainty set, i.e.",
    "a set of likely parameter values, can be considered, which includes the true parameters with high confidence based on the statistical estimation procedure.",
    "Then, the overall goal is to determine a revenue maximizing assortment while explicitly accounting for the uncertainty in the choice model parameters."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "The parameters of the choice model are mostly assumed to be unknown and thus need to be estimated from data, such that statistical errors in the parameters are unavoidable (Désir et al. 2023).",
    "The optimal assortment decision is then made based on the estimated parameter values while ignoring any uncertainty associated with these estimates (Rusmevichientong and Topaloglu 2012)."
